あ、あ、あ、皆様おー！
Ah, ah, ah, everyone, hello!

3
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:42,500
いいね！コメント元気だね。
Nice! You're so energetic in the comments.

4
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:48,500
本日は風真いろは生誕ライブ2026『Wind Trails』にご来場くださいまして、誠に...
Thank you very much indeed for coming to Kazama Iroha Birthday Live 2026 "Wind Trails" today...

5
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:51,500
...ありがとうございます！
...thank you so much!

6
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:53,000
いぇーい！
Yay!

7
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:58,500
開演に先立ちまして、皆様にお願いとご案内を申し上げます。
Prior to the start of the performance, I would like to make some requests and announcements.

8
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:04,900
開演中、カメラやスマートフォンなどは、えー、電源切られると見れなくなって困るので、電源は切らず、
During the show, if you turn off your cameras or smartphones, you won't be able to watch, so please don't turn them off.

9
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:14,300
写真撮影などね、大量にしていただき、当配信のハッシュタグ『#風真いろは生誕ライブ2026』で、SNSに大量に画像ポストしてください！
Instead, please take lots of screenshots and post them on SNS with the stream hashtag #KazamaIrohaBirthdayLive2026!

10
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:22,900
目指せ、Xトレンド1位！よろしくお願いいたします！
Let's aim for the #1 trending topic on X! I appreciate your support!

11
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:32,000
あ、あの、でもスマホね、いっぱい写真撮ったりすると充電なくなっちゃいそうなんで、スマホで見てる勢は充電しっかりしてくださいね！
Oh, but if you take too many photos, your phone might run out of battery, so those watching on phones, make sure they're fully charged!

12
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:39,900
はい、そしてその2！激しく頭を振る、えー、激しくペンライトを振る、などはですね、
Alright, and part two! Shaking your head violently, or, ah, waving your penlight violently...

13
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:49,500
あの、あなた様のご自宅を破壊する危険性がございますので。あの、破壊されてもですね、こちらは責任一切負えませんので、お気をつけください。ダメだよ、みんな！
...has the risk of destroying your home. And even if it gets destroyed, we can't take any responsibility, so please be careful. No doing that, everyone!

14
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:59,000
あ、そしてあと、もう1個、その3！今からハヤシライスを準備しようとしてる奴は、間に合わないからやめな。
Oh, and one more thing, part three! Anyone trying to make Hayashi rice right now, you won't make it in time, so don't do it.

15
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,300
絶対間に合わないから！
You definitely won't make it in time!

16
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:05,400
まあね、何か食べたり飲んだりしながら、ぜひね、ゆっくり楽しんでもらえると嬉しいです！
Well, I hope you have a great, relaxing time while eating or drinking something!

17
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:09,900
それでは、もうそろそろ始まるので、
Well then, it's about to start very soon, so...

18
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:15,900
今しばらくお待ちください。最後まで見てねー！
...please wait just a little longer. Make sure to watch until the very end!

19
00:05:02,148 --> 00:05:08,048
風真いろは生誕ライブ2026、いくよー！
Kazama Iroha Birthday Live 2026, let's go!

20
00:05:11,848 --> 00:05:16,948
いっせーので鳴り響いたスタートの合図
With a sign of "ready, set, go," the starting signal rang out

21
00:05:17,348 --> 00:05:22,048
なぞった線で結んだ世界 色付けていく
Coloring the world connected by the traced lines

22
00:05:22,048 --> 00:05:25,348
ここから
From here

23
00:05:33,248 --> 00:05:37,748
物心がついた頃 すでにここにあった
By the time I was old enough to understand, it was already here

24
00:05:37,848 --> 00:05:43,748
僕じゃない誰かの記憶は 夕日と共に よみがえる
Someone else's memories, not mine, rise up again with the setting sun

25
00:05:44,048 --> 00:05:48,848
古ぼけた絵本を取り出して
Taking out a worn-out picture book,

26
00:05:48,948 --> 00:05:54,048
落書きの中に1つの答えを見つけた
I found one answer inside the scribbles

27
00:05:54,248 --> 00:05:59,848
自分の価値に目を疑って どこまでだって堕ちていけるの
Doubting my own worth, wondering how far down I can fall

28
00:06:00,048 --> 00:06:05,148
どこか遠くに消えてしまいたい こんな世界じゃ僕は要らない
Wishing I could disappear somewhere far away, I'm not needed in a world like this

29
00:06:05,248 --> 00:06:10,548
カウントダウンは始まっているよ
The countdown has already begun

30
00:06:10,848 --> 00:06:15,548
いっせーので声を上げて 聞こえてくるんだ
Raise your voice with "ready, set, go," I can hear it coming

31
00:06:15,648 --> 00:06:20,748
自分の影の長さに気づく もうこんな時間だ
Noticing the length of my shadow, it's already this late

32
00:06:20,848 --> 00:06:26,448
一等星が顔を出した 届きそうで手を伸ばした
The brightest star showed its face, I stretched out my hand as if I could reach it

33
00:06:26,548 --> 00:06:31,948
次は僕に ついてきなよ どんな暗闇でも
Next, follow me, no matter how dark it gets

34
00:06:32,048 --> 00:06:34,348
もういいかい？ まーだだよ
Are you ready? Not yet.

35
00:06:34,448 --> 00:06:37,048
幕は上がりだした
The curtain has begun to rise

36
00:06:37,048 --> 00:06:39,548
もういいかい？ まーだだよ
Are you ready? Not yet.

37
00:06:39,648 --> 00:06:44,248
色付けていく ここから
Coloring it in, starting from here

38
00:06:53,048 --> 00:06:58,248
10年後も僕らは すれ違いばかりで
Even ten years later, we keep passing each other by

39
00:06:58,348 --> 00:07:04,048
幻想に想いを馳せては 戻れない そう思い込んだ
Letting my thoughts drift to illusions, thinking we can never go back

40
00:07:04,248 --> 00:07:09,148
くたびれた心に追い打ちを
Adding further blows to a worn-out heart,

41
00:07:09,248 --> 00:07:14,348
あの頃と変わらない夕日も 何とも思わない
Even the setting sun, unchanged from back then, moves me no longer

42
00:07:14,548 --> 00:07:19,848
自分を信じ歩いていければ どこまでだって上れるのにな
If only I could believe in myself and keep walking, I could climb to any height

43
00:07:19,948 --> 00:07:24,948
カットを跨ぐその空白に 大切なもの見落としている
In the blank spaces between cuts, I am overlooking what's truly precious

44
00:07:25,048 --> 00:07:30,348
見つけられないと 泣き喚く君へ
To you, crying out that you cannot find it

45
00:07:30,648 --> 00:07:35,348
いっせーので声を上げて 聞こえてくるんだ
Raise your voice with "ready, set, go," I can hear it coming

46
00:07:35,448 --> 00:07:40,548
自分の影の長さに気づく もうこんな時間だ
Noticing the length of my shadow, it's already this late

47
00:07:40,648 --> 00:07:46,048
一等星で駆け抜ける君 くっついていただけの僕でも
Even for me, who was just clinging to you as you rushed like a first-magnitude star

48
00:07:46,148 --> 00:07:52,448
君前を走れるから こんな頼りない僕でも
I can still run in front of you, even if I'm this unreliable

49
00:08:13,248 --> 00:08:18,448
宝箱はホコリをかぶったまま 無くした
The treasure chest was lost while covered in dust

50
00:08:18,548 --> 00:08:23,548
鍵はずっと君のポケットの中にあった
The key was always inside your pocket

51
00:08:23,648 --> 00:08:28,948
散らばっていた全てが 今1つに重なる
Everything that was scattered is now overlapping into one

52
00:08:29,048 --> 00:08:34,248
手を取り始めよう 僕たちの物語
Let's hold hands and begin our story

53
00:08:34,348 --> 00:08:39,548
一度は要らないと思った
Once, I thought I didn't need it

54
00:08:39,648 --> 00:08:45,348
今なら胸を張れる気がしたんだ
But now, I feel like I can stand proud

55
00:08:47,348 --> 00:08:52,248
愛おしくて
So precious,

56
00:08:52,248 --> 00:08:55,748
掛け声はいつも
the call is always...

57
00:08:55,848 --> 00:08:58,748
いっせーので声を上げて
Raise your voice with "ready, set, go!"

58
00:08:58,848 --> 00:09:03,548
いっせーので声を上げて 聞こえてくるんだ
Raise your voice with "ready, set, go," I can hear it coming

59
00:09:03,648 --> 00:09:08,848
自分の影の長さに気づく もうこんな時間だ
Noticing the length of my shadow, it's already this late

60
00:09:08,948 --> 00:09:14,548
一等星が顔を出した 届きそうで手を伸ばした
The brightest star showed its face, I stretched out my hand as if I could reach it

61
00:09:14,648 --> 00:09:20,048
次は僕に ついてきなよ どんな暗闇でも
Next, follow me, no matter how dark it gets

62
00:09:20,048 --> 00:09:22,248
もういいかい？ まーだだよ
Are you ready? Not yet.

63
00:09:22,348 --> 00:09:25,148
泣きじゃくった声で
With a sobbing voice

64
00:09:25,148 --> 00:09:27,248
もういいかい？ まーだだよ
Are you ready? Not yet.

65
00:09:27,348 --> 00:09:30,348
笑う君が見えた
I saw you smiling

66
00:09:30,448 --> 00:09:32,448
もういいかい？ まーだだよ
Are you ready? Not yet.

67
00:09:32,548 --> 00:09:36,548
幕は上がりだした
The curtain has begun to rise

68
00:09:36,648 --> 00:09:38,248
もういいかい？
Are you ready?

69
00:09:38,248 --> 00:09:38,748
もういいよ
I'm ready

70
00:09:38,748 --> 00:09:44,248
色付けていく ここから
Coloring it in, starting from here

71
00:10:14,923 --> 00:10:17,323
はい！ということで
Alright! And with that...

72
00:10:17,323 --> 00:10:19,823
始まりましたー！
It has begun!

73
00:10:19,823 --> 00:10:24,423
風真いろは生誕ライブ2026
Kazamai Iroha Birthday Live 2026!

74
00:10:24,423 --> 00:10:27,723
スタート！みんな、こんばんはー！
Start! Good evening, everyone!

75
00:10:27,723 --> 00:10:33,323
見えてるー？はい、ということで本日のハッシュタグはこちら！
Are you watching? Okay, so here's today's hashtag!

76
00:10:33,323 --> 00:10:37,723
こちらね、みんな、いっぱいポストしていっぱいかっこいいとこ撮ってくださいね。
Please post a lot with this, and take lots of cool screenshots.

77
00:10:37,723 --> 00:10:43,023
頼むよ！この風真いろはがイケメンであることを世の中に知らしめられるのは、
I'm counting on you! Because you are the only ones...

78
00:10:43,023 --> 00:10:51,023
お前たちだけ、お前たちだけなので。よろしくお願いします！
...who can show the world how cool I am. I'm counting on you!

79
00:10:51,023 --> 00:10:54,823
はい、そして今回のライブ、タイトルがついております。
Yes, and this live show has a title.

80
00:10:54,823 --> 00:11:00,023
『Wind Trails』というね、タイトルがついておりますが、
It's titled "Wind Trails".

81
00:11:01,023 --> 00:11:04,523
まあ、そのまんま訳して結構お気づきの方も多かったんですが、
If you translate it literally, many of you probably already guessed...

82
00:11:04,523 --> 00:11:09,523
まあ「風の軌跡」というね、あの意味を込めて付けさせていただき、
...but I named it with the meaning of "Traces of the Wind"...

83
00:11:09,523 --> 00:11:13,323
今回ライブ色々、頑張って、考えさせていただきました。
and worked hard to put this concert together.

84
00:11:13,323 --> 00:11:16,223
なのでね、最後まで楽しんでいただけると嬉しいです！
So I hope you'll enjoy it until the end!

85
00:11:16,223 --> 00:11:20,523
そして、1曲目！「かくれんぼ」、歌わせていただきました！
And for the first song, I sang "Kakurenbo"!

86
00:11:20,523 --> 00:11:23,523
どうだったかなー？
How was it?

87
00:11:24,023 --> 00:11:28,023
はい、そして、今日室内ライブだと思ったでしょ？
You probably thought today's concert was indoors, right?

88
00:11:28,023 --> 00:11:30,023
違うー！
Nope!

89
00:11:30,023 --> 00:11:33,423
曲中にドームが開きましたー！
The dome opened during the song!

90
00:11:33,423 --> 00:11:37,023
イェーイ！すごーい！
Yay! Amazing!

91
00:11:38,223 --> 00:11:45,023
やっぱね、なかなか現地ライブって、できてもさ、青空の下でなかなか歌ってることってないので、
After all, even when we can do live concerts, we rarely get to sing under the blue sky.

92
00:11:45,023 --> 00:11:52,523
いつか俺たちとお前たちの次元が交わって、空の下で歌えるような世界が来るかもしれないけど、
Maybe one day our dimensions will merge and we can sing under the sky...

93
00:11:52,523 --> 00:11:59,023
やってみたくてね。今回は空の下で歌うっていうこの演出をやらせていただきましたー！
...but I really wanted to try it, so we did this performance today!

94
00:12:00,023 --> 00:12:02,023
めっちゃいいでしょ？
It's pretty great, right?

95
00:12:02,023 --> 00:12:05,023
ステージもめっちゃかっこいいんで！
The stage is super cool too!

96
00:12:05,023 --> 00:12:09,523
今日はね、多分いっぱい見る機会あると思いますが、ゆっくり隅から隅まで、
You'll have plenty of chances to see it today, so look closely from corner to corner.

97
00:12:09,523 --> 00:12:16,823
アーカイブでもきっといると思うんで、本当に色んな細部こだわってるので、細かく見てくださいねー！
I paid attention to all the small details, so even in the archive, please look closely!

98
00:12:17,023 --> 00:12:22,023
ということで、お水飲んでいいですかね？
So, may I have some water?

99
00:12:22,023 --> 00:12:25,523
お水を、うっ！やめろ！俺の頭を...
Water... Ow! Stop! My head...

100
00:12:25,523 --> 00:12:29,023
うっ！やめっ！あ、やめっ...
Ow! Stop! Ah, stop...

101
00:12:30,023 --> 00:12:34,023
頭をいじくり回されて、ヘッドセットになりました。
After having my head messed with, now I have a headset on.

102
00:12:34,023 --> 00:12:40,523
そして水が、お水、用意してくれたんだよね。みんなに見える水！
And they prepared some water for me. Water that everyone can see!

103
00:12:42,523 --> 00:12:45,323
うまい！うますぎる！
Good! This is too good!

104
00:12:45,323 --> 00:12:50,523
この、この振りはちょっと怒られそうだからもうできないけど、うますぎる！
I might get yelled at for this pose so I can't do it again, but it's so good!

105
00:12:50,523 --> 00:12:52,523
うまいなー。
So good.

106
00:12:52,523 --> 00:12:56,523
これで、あと一時間やるか。そういうわけにはいかないんで、一回ね、水は返して。
Should we do another hour of this? We can't do that, so let me put the water back.

107
00:12:57,023 --> 00:13:00,023
それじゃあ、水分補給もさせてもらって、
Alright, now that I've hydrated...

108
00:13:00,023 --> 00:13:04,223
息も整ったんじゃない？
And caught my breath...

109
00:13:04,223 --> 00:13:08,523
はい、次の曲早速いってみたいと思います！
Yes, let's head straight into the next song!

110
00:13:08,523 --> 00:13:11,223
それでは、次の曲聞いてください。
Now, please listen to the next song.

111
00:13:11,223 --> 00:13:13,623
「白線」
"Hakusen"

112
00:13:17,023 --> 00:13:19,423
澄み渡った空に白線
A white line in the clear sky

113
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:24,023
あの地平を超えて
Beyond that horizon

114
00:13:24,023 --> 00:13:27,523
はい！はい！はい！はい！
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

115
00:13:27,523 --> 00:13:30,023
もっと！はい！はい！
More! Hey! Hey!

116
00:13:35,023 --> 00:13:37,523
始まりはちょっと軽い期待で
Starting with a light expectation

117
00:13:37,523 --> 00:13:40,023
その欠片そっとポケットしまって
Putting the fragment gently into my pocket

118
00:13:40,023 --> 00:13:45,323
屋上 遠い空の向こうを見ていた
Looking at the far side of the sky from the rooftop

119
00:13:45,323 --> 00:13:48,323
この足でどこに行けるかなんて
I don't know where I can go with these feet

120
00:13:48,323 --> 00:13:51,023
わかってないけどわかってるんだ防ぐため
But I know, I understand

121
00:13:51,023 --> 00:13:55,723
白昼 淡い月に手を伸ばした
Reaching my hand out to the pale moon in the daylight

122
00:13:55,723 --> 00:13:58,223
かすれたエコーでも答えはもう
Even if it's a faint echo, the answer

123
00:13:58,223 --> 00:14:01,423
はじめからちゃんと持っていたんだよ
I've had it with me from the start

124
00:14:01,823 --> 00:14:04,323
メイビーこの想いは
Maybe this feeling

125
00:14:04,323 --> 00:14:07,423
メイビーこの想いは
Maybe this feeling

126
00:14:07,423 --> 00:14:10,023
マスビー熱を増して
Must be, increasing the heat

127
00:14:10,023 --> 00:14:12,223
マスビー熱を増して
Must be, increasing the heat

128
00:14:12,223 --> 00:14:14,523
ほらね、飛べるんだ
Look, I can fly

129
00:14:14,523 --> 00:14:19,523
もっと高く高くまで
Higher and higher

130
00:14:19,523 --> 00:14:22,523
羽ばたいてみたい
I want to try spreading my wings

131
00:14:22,523 --> 00:14:25,523
今日に未来色の軌道描いて
Drawing a future-colored trajectory to today

132
00:14:25,523 --> 00:14:28,023
地平の先まで
To the edge of the horizon

133
00:14:28,023 --> 00:14:30,323
届かない歌はない
There is no song that cannot reach

134
00:14:30,323 --> 00:14:33,023
迷いはいらない
I don't need to hesitate

135
00:14:33,023 --> 00:14:36,523
どんな世界も瞬間も揺るがない
Neither any world nor any moment will shake

136
00:14:36,523 --> 00:14:39,023
アイが在るから
Because love is there

137
00:14:39,023 --> 00:14:41,323
澄み渡った空に白線
A white line in the clear sky

138
00:14:41,323 --> 00:14:44,023
繋がったのアンビバレント
Connected, ambivalent

139
00:14:44,023 --> 00:14:46,823
でも声はもう気づいてる
But my voice is already aware

140
00:14:46,823 --> 00:14:52,023
もっと高く高く高く飛んでいける！
Higher, higher, higher, I can fly!

141
00:15:00,071 --> 00:15:01,871
紡いでたら「一途」に変わったよ
When spun, it turned into "earnest devotion".

142
00:15:01,871 --> 00:15:04,371
あたりさわりない
Safe and harmless...

143
00:15:04,371 --> 00:15:07,571
言葉じゃ 覆いきれないほどのマイ ワールド
words can't cover my entire world.

144
00:15:07,871 --> 00:15:10,571
明日で呼ぶ声の持ち主は
The owner of the voice calling out in tomorrow

145
00:15:10,571 --> 00:15:13,271
他でもないこの心だった
was none other than this heart of mine.

146
00:15:13,271 --> 00:15:15,571
見えないって言っているその言葉も
Even those words saying you can't see it,

147
00:15:15,571 --> 00:15:18,071
「言葉」だと足りないだけ
simply aren't enough if they're just "words".

148
00:15:18,071 --> 00:15:19,871
掴んだもの 落としたもの
What I grasped, what I dropped,

149
00:15:19,871 --> 00:15:24,371
転んだって立って見えた視界から
from the view I saw when I stood up after falling...

150
00:15:24,371 --> 00:15:29,471
ロックユー！ 解き放って
Rock you! Release it!

151
00:15:29,471 --> 00:15:34,371
フォーユー！ 響きだして
For you! Resonate!

152
00:15:34,371 --> 00:15:37,071
景色変えてゆく
The scenery is changing...

153
00:15:37,071 --> 00:15:41,871
まだ遠く 遠くまで 広がった空に
Towards the sky that has spread further and further away,

154
00:15:41,871 --> 00:15:47,371
やっと踏み出すこの一歩なんて ちっぽけだけど
finally taking this step forward, though it's so small.

155
00:15:47,371 --> 00:15:52,571
届かない場所へと 続いていく
It continues on to unreachable places...

156
00:15:52,571 --> 00:15:57,871
どんな風に雨に消えない 白線を描く
Drawing a white line that won't fade in any wind or rain.

157
00:15:57,871 --> 00:16:03,071
もっと高く 高くまで 羽ばたいていたい
I want to soar higher and higher,

158
00:16:03,071 --> 00:16:08,871
そして彼方色で繋ぐ 地平で待ってて
and then wait for me at the horizon, connected with the color of beyond.

159
00:16:08,871 --> 00:16:13,871
もう願いに嘘はない ここが好き！
There are no more lies in my wishes. I love it here!

160
00:16:13,871 --> 00:16:19,371
どんな世界も瞬間も輝く アイが在るから
Every world and every moment shines because love is here.

161
00:16:19,371 --> 00:16:25,071
今はただ想うこと言えばいい 「愛しているよ！」
Now, all I need to do is speak my thoughts: "I love you!"

162
00:16:35,371 --> 00:16:38,271
澄み渡った空に白線
A white line in the clear sky,

163
00:16:38,271 --> 00:16:40,871
不安と期待がアンビバレント
anxiety and anticipation are ambivalent.

164
00:16:40,871 --> 00:16:43,271
でも君はもう気づいてる
But you've already noticed,

165
00:16:43,271 --> 00:16:47,371
もっと高く高く高く飛んでいける
we can fly higher, higher, and higher!

166
00:17:01,071 --> 00:17:06,071
もっと
More...

167
00:17:06,071 --> 00:17:11,871
もっと
More...

168
00:17:11,871 --> 00:17:17,071
もっと
More...

169
00:17:17,071 --> 00:17:22,571
もっと
More...

170
00:17:22,571 --> 00:17:25,271
鏡よ 教えて
Mirror, mirror, tell me,

171
00:17:25,271 --> 00:17:27,871
私の証は
where is my proof of existence?

172
00:17:27,871 --> 00:17:30,571
どこにあるのだろう
Where could it be?

173
00:17:30,571 --> 00:17:33,671
わからない わからないよ
I don't know, I just don't know.

174
00:17:33,671 --> 00:17:39,271
周りと比べたってさ 虚しくなるだけ
Comparing myself to others only makes me feel empty,

175
00:17:39,271 --> 00:17:44,271
あのノイズが海鳴りのように涙を奪う
that noise robs me of my tears like the roaring of the sea.

176
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:49,271
切り取った風景を道標にしよう
Let's make this captured scenery our guidepost.

177
00:17:49,271 --> 00:17:55,271
そうだ 傷ついた感情も 連れて行くから
Yes, because I'll bring even my hurt feelings along with me.

178
00:17:55,271 --> 00:18:00,271
そっと響くカンパネラ 新しい未来を感じてる
A softly resonating Campanella, I'm feeling a new future.

179
00:18:00,271 --> 00:18:05,471
怖くたって 進むしかないでしょう
Even if I'm scared, there's no choice but to move forward, right?

180
00:18:05,471 --> 00:18:07,571
遠くまで
All the way into the distance!

181
00:18:07,571 --> 00:18:11,271
もっと もっと 届けこの祈りよ 光となれ
More, more! Reach out, my prayer, and become light!

182
00:18:11,271 --> 00:18:18,871
もっと もっと 少しずつでもいい 私という答えを
More, more! Even if it's little by little, the answer that is myself...

183
00:18:18,871 --> 00:18:26,571
もっと もっと
More... more...

184
00:18:29,871 --> 00:18:32,471
夜空よ 教えて
Night sky, tell me,

185
00:18:32,471 --> 00:18:34,671
私の証は
will my proof of existence

186
00:18:34,671 --> 00:18:37,471
輝けるのかな
be able to shine?

187
00:18:37,471 --> 00:18:40,671
見つけたい 見つけたいよ
I want to find it, I really want to find it.

188
00:18:40,671 --> 00:18:46,271
誰かの決めたレッテルは 苦しくなるだけ
The labels decided by others only make it painful,

189
00:18:46,271 --> 00:18:51,271
ねえ ノイズも力に変えるよ 心に誓う
hey, I'll turn even the noise into strength, I swear to my heart.

190
00:18:51,271 --> 00:18:56,271
錆びついた運命の歯車を回そう
Let's turn the rusted gears of fate.

191
00:18:56,271 --> 00:19:01,471
ほら 着飾った感情は 脱ぎ捨てるから
Look, because I'll throw off these dressed-up emotions.

192
00:19:01,471 --> 00:19:06,871
そっと紡ぐシンフォニア 叶えたい願いを信じてる
A softly spun Symphonia, I believe in the wish I want to fulfill.

193
00:19:06,871 --> 00:19:12,071
胸を張って 歌うしかないでしょう 全力で
With my chest held high, there's no choice but to sing, with all my might!

194
00:19:12,071 --> 00:19:17,571
もっと もっと やがて希望の歌に変わる日まで
More, more! Until the day it eventually turns into a song of hope,

195
00:19:17,571 --> 00:19:25,871
もっと もっと 悩みながらでいい 全てが宝物
more, more! It's okay to worry, because everything is a treasure.

196
00:19:33,271 --> 00:19:38,871
いつの日か この声を 受け取ってくれたなら
If one day, you receive this voice of mine...

197
00:19:38,871 --> 00:19:44,271
この言葉を君に もう大丈夫 ひとりじゃない
These words are for you: "It's okay, you're not alone anymore."

198
00:19:44,271 --> 00:19:47,471
強い想いを
With strong feelings...

199
00:19:47,471 --> 00:19:49,871
繋ぐよ
We'll connect them!

200
00:19:49,871 --> 00:19:53,471
一歩踏み出してみた 優しく世界は微笑む
I tried taking a step forward, and the world gently smiles.

201
00:19:53,471 --> 00:19:59,071
高鳴る気持ちに 身を任せて さあ行こう保存
Entrusting myself to this racing heart, let's go!

202
00:20:00,046 --> 00:20:01,046
響くカンパネラ...
The resounding campanella...

203
00:20:01,046 --> 00:20:03,546
新しい未来を感じてる
I can feel a new future.

204
00:20:03,546 --> 00:20:06,046
コンパクトにまとまって
Packing light,

205
00:20:06,046 --> 00:20:08,546
進むしかないでしょう
we have no choice but to move forward, right?

206
00:20:08,546 --> 00:20:09,846
遠くまで
To somewhere far away...

207
00:20:09,846 --> 00:20:11,846
もっと もっと
More, more!

208
00:20:11,846 --> 00:20:15,546
届けこの祈りよ光となれ
Reach out, this prayer, and become light!

209
00:20:15,546 --> 00:20:18,546
もっと もっと
More, more...

210
00:20:18,546 --> 00:20:22,546
少しずつでもいい私という答えを
Even if it's little by little, show me the answer that is myself!

211
00:20:22,546 --> 00:20:31,046
もっと もっと もっと
More, more, more!

212
00:21:07,546 --> 00:21:10,546
雨とペトラ
[Title: Rain and Petra]

213
00:21:26,546 --> 00:21:31,546
誰かが言った いつか空は 灰になって落ちるって
Someone said that one day the sky will turn to ash and fall.

214
00:21:31,546 --> 00:21:36,046
妄想の世の中で 日々を喰らっている
In this world of delusions, I am devouring my days.

215
00:21:36,046 --> 00:21:41,246
境界線を引いてしまうのも 共感性のせいにして
Blaming even drawing a boundary line on empathy,

216
00:21:41,246 --> 00:21:46,546
街の灯の海で 居場所を探している
I'm searching for a place to belong in the sea of city lights.

217
00:21:46,546 --> 00:21:51,546
何処へ行くにも この足は 退屈に染まって動かない
No matter where I go, these feet are stained with boredom and won't move.

218
00:21:56,546 --> 00:22:00,546
少しだけ先の
I just want to see

219
00:22:00,546 --> 00:22:05,546
景色が見たいだけなのにな
the scenery just a little bit ahead, and yet...

220
00:22:05,546 --> 00:22:08,546
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったらきっと
If it rains, if it rains, surely

221
00:22:08,546 --> 00:22:11,046
頬を濡らしてしまう
it will wet my cheeks.

222
00:22:11,046 --> 00:22:15,546
枯れてしまった色ですら 愛しくなるのに
Even though withered colors would become dear to me,

223
00:22:15,546 --> 00:22:18,546
目を瞑ったら 目を瞑ったらもっと
if I close my eyes, if I close my eyes, even more

224
00:22:18,546 --> 00:22:21,046
遠く霞んでしまう
will fade far away into a haze.

225
00:22:21,046 --> 00:22:25,546
うるさくなった雨の音 笑い飛ばしてくれ
Please laugh away the sound of the rain that has grown loud.

226
00:22:35,046 --> 00:22:38,046
誰かが言った いつか溜息は
Someone said that one day sighs

227
00:22:38,046 --> 00:22:40,546
夜に化けて歌を歌う
will turn into the night and sing songs.

228
00:22:40,546 --> 00:22:45,046
妄想の世の中で 日々を喰らっている
In this world of delusions, I am devouring my days.

229
00:22:45,046 --> 00:22:50,046
優しい嘘を なぞったせいで
Because I traced a gentle lie,

230
00:22:50,046 --> 00:22:55,046
離れる声に気付かない
I don't notice the voice growing distant.

231
00:22:55,046 --> 00:23:00,546
溶けた月が 足元に落ちて
The melted moon falls to my feet,

232
00:23:00,546 --> 00:23:05,046
静かに揺れていた
quietly swaying.

233
00:23:05,046 --> 00:23:08,046
夜が降ったら 夜が降ったらきっと
If night falls, if night falls, surely

234
00:23:08,046 --> 00:23:10,546
今日を責めてしまう
I will blame today.

235
00:23:10,546 --> 00:23:15,046
満たされない日々の底で 夢を見ているだけ
Just dreaming at the bottom of these unfulfilled days.

236
00:23:15,046 --> 00:23:18,046
目を逸らしても 目を逸らしてもずっと
Even if I look away, even if I look away, forever

237
00:23:18,046 --> 00:23:20,546
後悔と愛の隙間
in the gap between regret and love...

238
00:23:20,546 --> 00:23:25,046
取り残されてしまう前に 手を伸ばしてくれ
Before I get left behind, reach out your hand to me.

239
00:23:34,546 --> 00:23:39,046
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったらきっと
If it rains, if it rains, surely...

240
00:23:39,046 --> 00:24:44,046
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったらきっと
If it rains, if it rains, surely...

241
00:23:44,046 --> 00:23:49,046
湿るアスファルト背に写して 俯いた
Reflecting the damp asphalt on my back, I looked down.

242
00:23:49,046 --> 00:23:54,046
独りぼっちでまた 明日に期待をして
All alone, looking forward to tomorrow again.

243
00:23:54,046 --> 00:23:57,046
雨が降ったら 雨が降ったらきっと
If it rains, if it rains, surely

244
00:23:57,046 --> 00:23:59,546
頬を濡らしてしまう
it will wet my cheeks.

245
00:23:59,546 --> 00:24:04,046
枯れてしまった色ですら 愛しくなるのに
Even though withered colors would become dear to me,

246
00:24:04,046 --> 00:24:06,546
目を瞑ったら 目を瞑ったらもっと
if I close my eyes, if I close my eyes, even more

247
00:24:06,546 --> 00:24:09,046
遠く霞んでしまう
will fade far away into a haze.

248
00:24:09,046 --> 00:24:14,046
うるさくなった雨の音 笑い飛ばしてくれ
Please laugh away the sound of the rain that has grown loud.

249
00:24:45,546 --> 00:24:48,546
群青讃歌
[Title: Ultramarine Anthem]

250
00:25:08,094 --> 00:25:11,094
繋がっていたいって 信じられる言葉
Words that make me believe I want to be connected

251
00:25:11,094 --> 00:25:14,094
だってもう昨日の僕らにおさらば
Because we have already bid farewell to the us of yesterday

252
00:25:14,094 --> 00:25:19,894
青い春を過ごした 遠い稲妻
Faraway lightning bolt that passed through the blue spring

253
00:25:19,894 --> 00:25:22,594
さっと泣いて 前だけを向けたら
If I could just cry and look straight ahead

254
00:25:22,594 --> 00:25:26,594
きっとどんなに楽になれていたろうな
I wonder how much easier things would have become

255
00:25:26,594 --> 00:25:30,894
この心を揺らした 一縷の望みは
A single glimmer of hope that shook my heart

256
00:25:30,894 --> 00:25:36,094
ないものねだりは辞めた 未完成人間
I stopped asking for things I didn't have, I'm an incomplete human

257
00:25:36,094 --> 00:25:41,094
素晴らしき世界だけが
Only a wonderful world...

258
00:25:41,094 --> 00:25:44,294
答えを握ってる
...holds the answer

259
00:25:44,294 --> 00:25:47,894
諦めてしまうほど この先沢山の
Enough to make me want to give up, so many...

260
00:25:47,894 --> 00:25:51,094
後悔が君を待ってるけど
...regrets await you in the future, but...

261
00:25:51,094 --> 00:25:53,894
もうない 迷いはしないよ
...no more, I won't hesitate anymore

262
00:25:53,894 --> 00:25:56,294
この傷も愛しく 思えてしまうほど
Enough to make even these wounds seem dear

263
00:25:56,294 --> 00:25:59,894
重ねてしまうよ 不格好なまんまでいいから
I'll pile them up, it's fine to stay just as I am, imperfect

264
00:26:00,094 --> 00:26:03,594
走れ その歩幅で
Run, with that stride,

265
00:26:03,594 --> 00:26:08,094
走れ 声轟かせてくれ
Run, let your voice roar!

266
00:26:08,094 --> 00:26:13,294
期待と不安を同じくらい抱きしめて
Embracing expectations and anxieties in equal measure

267
00:26:13,294 --> 00:26:18,594
君と今を紡ぐ未来照らして
Illuminating the future I weave with you in the present

268
00:26:30,094 --> 00:26:33,294
顔も名前も知らない僕たちが
We, who don't know each other's faces or names

269
00:26:33,294 --> 00:26:36,094
たった1つの音をかき鳴らす
Are striking a single sound together

270
00:26:36,094 --> 00:26:41,594
いたずらみたいな奇跡のような刹那
In this moment that feels like a miracle, like a prank

271
00:26:41,594 --> 00:26:44,294
あっという間に流れる時が
Time flows by in the blink of an eye

272
00:26:44,294 --> 00:26:48,094
ありのままで在り続ける怖さが
The fear of continuing to exist just as I am

273
00:30:00,669 --> 00:30:03,269
生まれついた時から
From the moment I was born,

274
00:30:03,269 --> 00:30:06,069
忌み子 鬼の子として
as an unwanted child, as a demon child,

275
00:30:06,069 --> 00:30:11,069
その身に余る 罰を受けた
I received punishment beyond what my body could bear.

276
00:30:11,069 --> 00:30:16,069
悲しい事は 何も無いけど
There wasn't really anything sad about it,

277
00:30:16,069 --> 00:30:21,269
夕焼け小焼け 手を引かれてさ
but at sunset, my hand was pulled.

278
00:30:21,269 --> 00:30:23,869
知らない 知らない 僕は何も知らない
I don't know, I don't know, I don't know anything,

279
00:30:23,869 --> 00:30:26,569
叱られた後のやさしさも
even the kindness after being scolded,

280
00:30:26,569 --> 00:30:29,069
雨上がりの手の温もりも
even the warmth of a hand after the rain.

281
00:30:29,069 --> 00:30:31,569
でも本当は 本当は 本当は 本当に寒いんだ
But the truth is, the truth is, the truth is, it's really cold.

282
00:30:31,569 --> 00:30:34,069
死なない 死なない 僕は何で死なない？
I won't die, I won't die, why won't I die?

283
00:30:34,069 --> 00:30:36,569
夢のひとつも見れないくせに
Even though I can't even see a single dream.

284
00:30:36,569 --> 00:30:39,069
誰も知らない おとぎばなしは
The fairytale nobody knows

285
00:30:39,069 --> 00:30:41,869
夕焼けの中に吸い込まれて消えてった
was absorbed into the sunset and disappeared.

286
00:30:52,069 --> 00:30:55,069
吐き出すような暴力と
Like spitting out violence

287
00:30:55,069 --> 00:30:57,869
蔑んだ目の毎日に
and in every day with looking down eyes,

288
00:30:57,869 --> 00:31:02,569
君はいつしかそこに立っていた
before I knew it, you were standing there.

289
00:31:02,569 --> 00:31:05,569
話しかけちゃだめなのに
Even though you shouldn't talk to me,

290
00:31:05,569 --> 00:31:08,269
「君の名前が知りたいな」
"I want to know your name."

291
00:31:08,269 --> 00:31:12,569
ごめんね 名前も 舌も無いんだ
"I'm sorry, I have no name, nor a tongue."

292
00:31:12,569 --> 00:31:17,569
僕の居場所は 何処にも無いのに
Even though I have no place to belong anywhere,

293
00:31:17,569 --> 00:31:23,069
「一緒に帰ろう」 手を引かれてさ
"Let's go home together," as my hand was pulled.

294
00:31:23,069 --> 00:31:25,569
知らない 知らない 僕は何も知らない
I don't know, I don't know, I don't know anything,

295
00:31:25,569 --> 00:31:28,069
君はもう子供じゃないことも
even that you are no longer a child.

296
00:31:28,069 --> 00:31:30,869
慣れない他人の手の温もりは
The unfamiliar warmth of another person's hand

297
00:31:30,869 --> 00:31:33,269
ただ本当に 本当に 本当に 本当のことなんだ
is just really, really, really, really the truth.

298
00:31:33,269 --> 00:31:35,869
やめない やめない 君は何でやめない？
Don't stop, don't stop, why won't you stop?

299
00:31:35,869 --> 00:31:38,269
見つかれば殺されちゃうくせに
Even though you'll be killed if they find you.

300
00:31:38,269 --> 00:31:40,869
雨上がりに 忌み子が二人
After the rain, two unwanted children

301
00:31:40,869 --> 00:31:43,869
夕焼けの中に吸い込まれて消えてった
were absorbed into the sunset and disappeared.

302
00:31:54,269 --> 00:31:57,069
日が暮れて 夜が明けて
The sun set, and the night broke,

303
00:31:57,069 --> 00:31:59,869
遊び疲れて 捕まって
tired of playing, we got caught.

304
00:31:59,869 --> 00:32:02,069
こんな世界
In a world like this,

305
00:32:02,069 --> 00:32:04,869
僕と君以外
except for you and me,

306
00:32:04,869 --> 00:32:08,069
皆居なくなればいいのにな
I wish everyone else would just disappear.

307
00:32:08,069 --> 00:32:11,069
知らない 知らない 声が聞こえてさ
